Bio: Kamal Haasan is an Indian actor, dancer, film director, screenwriter, producer, playback singer, lyricist and politician who works primarily in Tamil cinema. His production company, Raaj Kamal Films International, has produced several of his films. He has won four National Film Awards and 19 Filmfare Awards. He was awarded the Kalaimamani award in 1984 the Padma Shri in 1990, the Padma Bhushan in 2014 and the Ordre des Arts et des Lettres (Chevalier) in 2016.[6] He was awarded the Lifetime Achievement Award at 15th Mumbai International Film Festival in 2013.[7]
